      "instruction": "<p>Add the contents of your pan to the <strong>slow cooker</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>pepper strips </strong>and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>carrot </strong>with 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, the<strong> beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste </strong>and<strong> Henderson's Relish</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong>, then cover and cook on high for 4 hours – this is your <strong>beef goulash</strong></p>",
